mappings.name: Gets the metadata of a specific report.

schema.description: A report's metadata including the URL from which the report itself can be downloaded.

createTime.description: The date/time when this report was created.

downloadUrl.description: The URL from which the report can be downloaded (max. 1000 characters).

endTime.description: The end of the time period that the report instance covers. The value is exclusive.

id.description: The server-generated ID of the report.

jobExpireTime.description: The date/time when the job this report belongs to will expire/expired.

jobId.description: The ID of the job that created this report.

startTime.description: The start of the time period that the report instance covers. The value is inclusive.

nextPageToken.description: A token to retrieve next page of results. Pass this value in the ListReportsRequest.page_token field in the subsequent call to `ListReports` method to retrieve the next page of results.

schema.description: A job creating reports of a specific type.

createTime.description: The creation date/time of the job.

expireTime.description: The date/time when this job will expire/expired. After a job expired, no new reports are generated.

id.description: The server-generated ID of the job (max. 40 characters).

name.description: The name of the job (max. 100 characters).

reportTypeId.description: The type of reports this job creates. Corresponds to the ID of a ReportType.

systemManaged.description: True if this a system-managed job that cannot be modified by the user; otherwise false.
